      <description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;hr&gt;Gukkor wrote:&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xD;
&lt;p&gt;"It would appear the sleeper is the drakota"&lt;/p&gt;&#xD;
&lt;p&gt;No, the Drakota isn't an individual, it's a race.&amp;nbsp; The Drakota are a hidden race of dragonkin that serve as the covert&amp;nbsp;agents of the dragons, unleashed only for special missions of great importance.&amp;nbsp; A group of them is sent to assassinate Vox and Nagafen, but only succeeds in taking out the former.&amp;nbsp; The events in this book take place many years after the Sleeper has awakened and disappeared.&amp;nbsp; The&amp;nbsp;Ring of Scale&amp;nbsp;has no control over him.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;Yeah, the current EQ2 plotline deals very heavily with the Sleeper, who pretty much conclusively blew up Luclin, but also may still be alive. There's a couple factions in the former Plane of Sky, the first main one being the Doomwing Legion under Lord Vyemm who believes the prophecy of the sleeper's return is pretty much metaphorical and the Sleeper himself is never coming back. The second one is Harla Dar who is fanatically devoted to Kerafyrm and awaits his return. There's others, like Gore/Talendor and Venekor, but I'm not entirely clear on their standing.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Darathar was a dragon that had control of the Harness, a magical item that gives the user power over the drakota. He used this to attack Naggy and Vox since dragons don't attack each other directly. The current owner of the Harness is unknown as far as I know.&lt;br&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
